  "title": "Contract Communications Strategy & Engagement (Central) #HMS",
  "description": "<h2>Contract Communications Strategy & Engagement (Strategic Engagement)</h2><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 year (January 2026 – December 2026)<br /><strong>Nearest MRT:</strong> Raffles Place<br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday to Friday, 8:30 AM – 6:00 PM<br /><strong>Salary</strong>: Min Degree Holder: <strong>$15/hr</strong></p><h3>Job Responsibilities</h3><p>1. Content Development & Channel Growth</p><ul><li><p>Plan, create, and publish <strong>a minimum of four content pieces per week</strong> to sustain and grow engagement across labour movement–based social media channels.</p></li><li><p>Track and analyse performance metrics, refining content strategies to maximise reach and audience growth.</p></li></ul><p>2. Podcast Logistics & Administration</p><ul><li><p>Coordinate logistics, scheduling, and administrative briefings for the development and potential launch of a labour movement podcast series.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with internal stakeholders and external partners to ensure smooth execution of production and operational requirements.</p></li></ul><p>3. Community & Network Expansion</p><ul><li><p>Drive outreach initiatives and build collaborations with Institutes of Higher Learning (IHLs) to support the expansion of the YC3 creator network.</p></li><li><p>Contribute towards the strategic goal of growing the creator network to <strong>100 creators by end of H2 2026</strong>.<br /><br />Interested candidates, do submit your resume to: jocelynchan@recruitexpress.com.sg OR telegram @jocelynchan</p><p></p><p>Jocelyn Chan| Consultant | Recruit Express Pte Ltd (Healthcare & Lifescience)</p><p>Company EA Licence number : 99C4599</p><p>Personnel EA License: R1331820</p><p></p></li></ul>",
